b'' b'greetings netters,' b'' b'steve writes <about cobra locks' b'' b'well i have the mother of all locks. on friday the 16th of april i took' b'possesion of a cobra links lock, diameter. this was a special order.' b'' b'i weighs a lot. i had to carry it home and it was digging into my shoulder' b'after about two blocks.' b'' b'i have currently a kryptonite rock lock through the front wheel, a hd' b'padlock for the steering lock, a master padlock to lock the cover to two' b'front spokes, and the cobra links through the rear swing arm and around a' b'post in an underground parking garage.' b'' b'next friday the 30th i have an appointment to have an alarm installed on' b'me bike.' b'' b'when i travel the cobra links and the cover and padlock stay at home.' b'' b'by the way. i also removed the plastic mesh that is on the cobra links' b'and encased the lock from end to end using bicycle inner tubes (two of' b'them) i got the from bicycle dealer that sold me the cobra links. the' b"guys were really great and didn't mark up the price of the lock much" b'and the inner tubes were free.' b'' b'later.' b'' b'-------------------------------------------------------------------------------' b"1992 fxstc rock 'n roll mike mychalkiw" b'hog ryerson polytechnical institute b'dod just this side of hell. academic computing information centre' 